[1] Cholera - Korea ex Philippines
Date: Mon, 4 Jul 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: The Korea Times [edited]
<http://times.hankooki.com/lpage/nation/200507/kt2005070422094911990.htm>

Tourist Infected With Cholera
------------------------------
Quarantine officials announced yesterday, 3 Jul 2005, that a Korean man who
returned from the Philippines was found to be infected with cholera,
calling for [more stringent] hygienic [rules].
"A Korean male tourist, who is in quarantine now, has shown some symptoms
of cholera such as diarrhea and high fever when he returned home on 30 Jun
2005," Park Sun-hee, an official at the state-run Korea Center for Disease
Control and Prevention (KCDC), told The Korea Times. She added that the
patient in his 30s has almost completely recovered from the illness.
Park said that the KCDC is conducting an epidemiological test of the germ
carrier as well as the tourist's family members. She said KCDC officials
are also trying to find out the source of the virus. The official added
that it is in the process of testing 234 passengers and crew members still
in Korea who were on the same flight.
No additional cholera patient has been reported yet, but people who are
traveling to Southeast Asian countries should remain on alert, according to
the quarantine office. The disease control agency advised people to drink
boiled water, eat well-cooked food and wash hands before having meals to
avoid cholera infection.
[Byline: Kim Cheong-won]
