[4] Gastroenteritis, fatal - Pakistan (Balochistan)
Date: Thu, 7 Jul 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Islamic Republic News Agency [edited]
<http://www.irna.ir/en/news/view/menu-235/0507070818170515.htm>

Gastroenteritis kills 18 in Pakistan
-------------------------------------
At least 18 people have died from gastroenteritis in a remote town in
Pakistan's Balochistan province, reports and doctors said on Thu, 7 Jul 2005.
The disease has spread in Zhob city, some 250 northeast of the provincial
capital Quetta, and its adjoining areas, Doctor Rahim in the local
government hospital said. Children and women are also among the victims,
private ARY TV channel quoted Rahim as saying. Many others have also been
affected, according to the report.
Rahim said that emergency has been declared in the local hospital but added
that the hospital is running out of medicines to deal with the epidemic. He
appealed to the provincial government and the health department to
immediately send medical teams and more medicines. The doctor said scores
of new gastroenteritis-affected patients daily come to hospital, and the
lone government hospital is facing problems to deal with the situation.
--
