[6] Cholera - Guinea
Date: Thu, 7 Jul 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Today Online [edited]
<http://www.todayonline.com/articles/60239.asp>

Cholera outbreak in Guinea kills 21
-----------------------------------
21 people have died in western and central Guinea in a new cholera outbreak
that has infected 345 people since 15 Jun 2005, the health ministry said in
a statement broadcast over public radio. Clinicians and emergency services
have been rushed to the infected areas, which include the capital Conakry.
Guinea is the latest country in West Africa to be hit by an outbreak of the
water-borne illness, which is transmitted through poor hygiene in food
preparation and sanitation.
--
